<topic id="d705776c-9eb8-4861-bb08-fdcaf7905d79" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerConceptualDocument
    xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
		<introduction>
			<para>Adding a new color to an existing font in the application can be accomplished through this feature. Colors are a collection of ordered effects. Effects in colors occur at the end of every layer in a variant.</para>
			<para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image placement="center" xlink:href="Add-New-Color"/>
				</mediaLink>
			</para>
		</introduction>
		<section address="EffectsContextMenu">
			<title>Effects Context Menu</title>
			<content>
				<para>Right-clicking the effects area exposes the following context menu actions:</para>
				<list class="ordered">
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Add Effect</legacyBold>: This feature adds a new effect to the stack.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Edit Effect</legacyBold>: This feature edits an existing effect in the stack.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Move Effect Up</legacyBold>: This feature moves an effect ahead of other effects.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Move Effect Down</legacyBold>: This feature moves an effect after other effects.
						</para>
					</listItem>
					<listItem>
						<para>
							<legacyBold>Remove Effect</legacyBold>: This feature removes an existing effect.
						</para>
					</listItem>
				</list>
			</content>
		</section>
		<relatedTopics />
	</developerConceptualDocument>
</topic>
